<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6922] JsonSlurper loses trailing 0&apos;s in numbers (regression in Groovy 2.3)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6922</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In previous versions of Grails before JsonSlurper was significantly changed, this test passed. However, it fails in Groovy 2.3.x (tested up to 2.3.3).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;void testParseNumWithDecimals() {
   def i = parser.parseText(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;123.40&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)
   BigDecimal i2 = 123.40G
   &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; BigDecimal
   &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; i == i2
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This test should be added to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/blob/GROOVY_2_3_X/subprojects/groovy-json/src/test/groovy/groovy/json/JsonSlurperTest.groovy&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/blob/GROOVY_2_3_X/subprojects/groovy-json/src/test/groovy/groovy/json/JsonSlurperTest.groovy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Groovy 2.3.3, the assertion fails as i = 123.4G, not 123.40G.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
